{"type":"message","id":"f5d9fc78","parentId":"acda678a","timestamp":"2026-04-22T05:49:14.966Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"好的，现在需要更新步骤编号，原来的4→5，5→6，6→6.1（扩展），7→7，8→8。让我先更新执行选项部分。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019db3bc302979f640652608fc5a292f","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### 6) Offer execution options\n\nOffer one of these choices (numbered so users can reply with a single digit):\n\n1. Do it for me (guided, step-by-step approvals)\n2. Show plan only\n3. Fix only critical issues\n4. Export commands for later","newText":"### 6) Offer execution options (enhanced)\n\nOffer one of these choices (numbered so users can reply with a single digit):\n\n1. Full manual execution (guided, step-by-step approvals)\n2. **Auto-fix safe items only** (new - fixes all auto-safe category items automatically)\n3. **Semi-automatic fix** (new - auto-risk items require confirmation but execute automatically)\n4. Show plan only\n5. Fix only critical issues\n6. Export commands for later\n\n#### 6.1) Auto-fix safe items (option 2)\n\nWhen user selects option 2:\n1. Display all auto-safe items to be fixed\n2. Create backup of all files to be modified\n3. Run auto-safe scripts in sequence:\n   ```bash\n   # Example auto-safe scripts\n   scripts/auto-safe/fix-openclaw-perms.sh\n   scripts/auto-safe/fix-logging-perms.sh\n   ```\n4. Verify each fix succeeded\n5. Report results with rollback instructions\n\nAuto-safe scripts characteristics:\n- Always create backup before modification\n- Use non-destructive operations\n- Provide rollback instructions in output\n- Generate logs in `/tmp/openclaw-*.log`\n- Exit on error with clear message"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"glm-4-7-251222","usage":{"input":411,"output":457,"cacheRead":53248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54116,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRe